We recommended that:

The Municipal Mayor direct the Inventory Committee to complete the conduct of the physical inventory of the Municipality’s PPE and submit to the Audit Team the properly accomplished RPCPPE;

The RPCPPE shall be reconciled with the accounting records in order to ensure that the PPE account balances are fairly presented in the financial statements. The discrepancies should be investigated and necessary adjustments should be made to come up with a complete and accurate balance of asset accounts, PPE in the financial statements;

The Accounting Office should religiously maintain the PPELC to provide a detailed information of the PPE which can be of great importance in the conduct of the physical inventory;


The Municipal General Services Officer Designate of the Municipality maintain Property Cards and provide/attach property sticker to each PPE item for ease of reference and property tagging;

Management give considerable time and additional personnel to work on the reconciliation of the of the physical count with the accounting records and the subsequent inventory tagging of all PPE and assignment of property codes for a more facilitative identification and tracking of the location of the properties.  Inventory Tag should be attached to the newly acquired equipment before these are distributed to the intended end-users;

A Municipal Valuation Committee be created to determine the appraised value of donated properties and those properties found on station during the inventory taking so that these properties can be correctly recorded in the books of accounts of the municipality; and

Henceforth, inventory taking and reconciliation of related subsidiary records should be regularly undertaken and regarded with utmost importance.

